The low number of people turning out to register as voters in Kirinyaga county has forced aspirants to change tact and engage in a door-to-door campaigns.They include woman representative aspirant Rose Muguchu, Ndia parliamentary hopeful Muteti Murimi and Wangui Ngirici, who is running for woman rep. ''Starting Monday [yesterday], I will offer transport to the elderly who cannot go a long distance so that they can get enlisted,'' Muguchu said on Sunday.